<section class="row" id="leader">
<div class="branches"></div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
      <h1>Kevin &amp; Emily</h1>
      <span class="subby">are getting married on</span>
      <h2>26th September 2014</h2>
      <span class="subby">at</span>
      <h3>The Crazy Bear, Stadhampton, Oxfordshire</h3>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container rsvp">

    <!-- new user -->
    <div class="rsvpstep col-sm-12" ng-if="state == 0">
      <a ng-click="showSigninForm()" class="btn btn-default btn-outline btn-lg"><span class="fa fa-check-square-o"></span> RSVP</a>
    </div>

    <!-- user login form -->
    <div class="rsvpstep col-sm-12 clearfix" ng-if="state == 1" ng-animate=" 'animate' ">

      <form class="col-sm-6 well">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Username</label>
          <input type="text" class="form-control" name="username" ng-model="user.username">
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Password</label>
          <input type="password" class="form-control" name="password" ng-model="user.password">
        </div>

        <button ng-click="signin(user)" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Login</button>
      </form>

    </div>

    <!-- user logged in -->
    <div class="rsvpstep col-sm-12" ng-if="state == 2">

      <div class="clearfix">
        <form class="">
          <div ng-repeat="groupy in users">

            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <div class="well">
                <h3>{{ groupy.username }}</h3>

                <p>I would like to attend...</p>

                <div class="checkbox" ng-if="groupy.invite.ceremony">
                  <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" name="ceremony" ng-checked="groupy.rsvp.ceremony" ng-model="groupy.rsvp.ceremony"> ceremony
                  </label>
                </div>

                <div class="checkbox" ng-if="groupy.invite.reception">
                  <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" name="reception" ng-checked="groupy.rsvp.reception" ng-model="groupy.rsvp.reception"> reception
                  </label>
                </div>

                <div class="checkbox" ng-if="groupy.invite.party">
                  <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" name="party" ng-checked="groupy.rsvp.party" ng-model="groupy.rsvp.party"> party
                  </label>
                </div>

                <div class="rsvpactions">
                  <button ng-click="updateUser(groupy)" ng-disabled="form.$invalid || isUnchanged(groupy)" class="btn btn-primary btn-md">Update RSVP</button>
                  <br>
                </div>

                <div class="col-sm-12 clearfix">
                  <small class="pull-right">Last updated {{ groupy.updated | amCalendar }}</small>
                </div>

              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

        </form>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12">
      <div class="rsvpactions pull-right">
        <button ng-click="update(users)" ng-disabled="form.$invalid || isUnchanged(users)" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Update everyone's RSVP</button>
        <br>
        <a href="/signout" class="btn btn-sm pull-right">Sign out</a>
      </div>

      <div class="rsvpinfo col-sm-12">
        <p>Please RSVP by July 11<sup>th</sup> 2014</p>
      </div>
    </div>


  </div>
</div>
</section>



<section class="row" id="couple">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
      <h3>About the couple</h3>

      <div class="couple-images">
        <div class="emily"></div>
        <div class="kevin"></div>
      </div>

      <p>We met at Oxford Brookes University in 2006.</p>

      <p>It's remarkable, really, that alongside the long hours of lectures and copious coursework assignments, we still found several hours a day to play pool together at the student bar. It was meant to be.</p>

      <p>We lived together in Oxford for a further 7 years. In this time we graduated from uni, got jobs, ate a lot and got fat, ran a lot and got thin and watched every TV show Joss Whedon has ever created.  Several times.</p>

      <p>Last year, we took a trip to the Cotswolds Wildlife park.  It rained all day, and so we found ourselves in our waterproofs, sheltering under a tree next to the red pandas. It was here Kevin proposed.  And got a very wet knee for it too.  Aww.....</p>

      <p>As most of you will know, we are not organised people.  And apparently, planning a wedding takes loads of time and hard work - who knew?  Luckily we've had many friends and family around to encourage us, support us, and basically give us a well needed kick up the arse.  Huge thanks to you all and we can't wait for you to join us in our celebration.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>




